LatexCommand cite
key "belling98b,ParaGaussV3.1"

\end_inset

.
 There are several possibilities, of increasing accuracy and expected computatio
nal effort, for implementing the long-range electrostatic interaction of
 the electrons of the QM sub-system with the charges of the solvent, represented
 by site distribution densities:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the multipole expansion (MPE) of the Coulomb potential of the QM subsystem,
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the fitting function representation of the electronic density 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "dunlap-mintmire90,dunlap-roesch90"

\end_inset

