\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the electronic density directly derived from the Kohn--Sham wave function.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each of the three choices implies a specific contribution to the one-electron
 Hamiltonian of the QM subsystem and to the solute-induced field to which
 the solvent molecules are exposed to.
 At least the first two of these strategies of increasing accuracy and computati
onal demand will be implemented and evaluated regarding their performance
 and accuracy implications for a mutually consistent reaction field approach.
 For practical applications an efficient and scaling parallelization of
 these approaches will be crucial.
 A related issue is the derivation of the site-site force-field parameterization
