\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Canonical distribution of the compound system is given by the distribution
 function
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\rho(X,Y)=\mathrm{e}^{\beta(A-V(X,Y))}\label{eq:def-partition-function}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

with the free energy 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 of the system defined from normalization condition for distribution density
 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "book:landauV5"

\end_inset

