\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
A=-\beta^{-1}\ln\int\mathrm{e}^{-\beta V(X,Y)}dXdY
\end{equation}

\end_inset

The (reduced) distribution of the solute coordinates
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\rho(X)=\int\rho(X,Y)dY
\end{equation}

\end_inset

may be used to introduce the free energy 
\begin_inset Formula $A(X)$
\end_inset

 of a solute conformation 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\rho(X)=\mathrm{e}^{\beta(A-A(X))}\label{eq:def-conformation-free-energy}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

more explicitly given by given by a partial statistical sum over solvent
