\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{dA(X)}{dX}=\left\langle \frac{\partial V}{\partial X}\right\rangle _{X}:=\int\frac{\partial V}{\partial X}\rho_{X}(Y)dY
\]

\end_inset

where we introduced conditional distribution function
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\rho_{X}(Y):=\frac{\rho(X,Y)}{\rho(X)}=\mathrm{e}^{\beta[A(X)-V(X,Y)]}
\]

\end_inset

representing normalized solvent distribution for specific parameters 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

.
 For exploration of the free-energy surface 
\begin_inset Formula $A(X)$
\end_inset

 this implies that the energy derivatives 
