\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In practice the integration over solvent coordinates 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 is often not performed explicitly.
 One rather estimates the integrals using ensemble averages with associated
 approximation 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\rho}(X,Y)$
\end_inset

 for distribution function 
\series bold

\begin_inset Formula $\rho(X,Y)$
\end_inset


\series default
.
