\begin_layout Standard
Quantum mechanics suggests that the electrons interact with other charged
 species by an additive Coulomb law.
 We take that additivity over to the case of solute-solvent model interactions
 literally and knowingly that this is rather a convenient approximation
 given the way the solvent molecules are represented.
