.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 This approximation can be tuned by choosing an effective interaction instead
 of the Coulomb law as is customary, for example, in the effective core
 potential (ECP) models.
 An expectation value of a general spin-free multiplicative one-electron
 operator 
\begin_inset Formula $v(\vec{r})$
\end_inset

 is a linear functional of the density 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 given by a trace integral: 
\begin_inset Formula $\langle v\rangle=\int v(\vec{r})n(\vec{r})d^{3}r$
\end_inset

.
 This will be also the case for an interaction with a single solvent site,
 or any number of the solvent sites, or even a mean field of the solvent
 in this section.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Assuming the interaction of an electron at position 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{r}$
\end_inset

