\begin_layout Standard
The techniques for numeric evaluation of these convolution integrals will
 necessarily depend on the asymptotic properties of the convolution kernel.
 One of the primary difficulties for numeric evaluations is the Coulomb
 tail of the kernel: 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{\alpha}(r)\sim-z_{\alpha}/r$
\end_inset

, for 
\begin_inset Formula $r\to\infty$
\end_inset

.
 For this situation it is advantageous to have an analytic expression for
 the Fourier transforms of the long-range asymptotics.
 A sufficiently smooth short range interaction, on the other hand, may be
 efficiently treated by FFT techniques.
